                                                   Mahesh out, Yuki in semi-finals

           
	Melbourne: Mahesh Bhupathi and Mark Knowles suffered a straight-set loss in the Australian Open mens doubles semi-final on Thursday. 
    
	But there was some good news for India as Yuki Bhambri beat third seed Daniel Evans of Britain 7-6 (7-5), 4-6, 6-3 to enter the last four of boys singles. 
    
	The eighth seed will clash with local challenger Bernard Tomic, the No. 5 seed who shocked top seed Cesar Ramirez of Mexico 6-3, 6-4. 
    
	A day after knocking out top seeds and world No. 1 pair Bob and Mike Bryan, Bhupathi and Knowles lost 4-6, 4-6 to Israeli eighth seeds Jonathan Erlich and Andy Ram. 
    
	Erlich and Ram will take on Arnaud Clement and Michael Llodra in the summit clash. The seventh-seeded French pair saw off South Africans Jeff Coetzee and Wesley Moodie 6-3, 7-6 (11-9). (PTI) 
                                                   
